title: Google\Cloud\Dataproc\V1\KubernetesClusterConfig
name: KubernetesClusterConfig
description:
The configuration for running the Dataproc cluster on Kubernetes.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dataproc.v1.KubernetesClusterConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.kubernetes_namespace
params.description: Optional. A namespace within the Kubernetes cluster to deploy into. If this namespace does not exist, it is created. If it exists, Dataproc verifies that another Dataproc VirtualCluster is not installed into it. If not specified, the name of the Dataproc Cluster is used.

params.name: data.gke_cluster_config
params.description: Required. The configuration for running the Dataproc cluster on GKE.

params.name: data.kubernetes_software_config
params.description: Optional. The software configuration for this Dataproc cluster running on Kubernetes.
